narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained a deeper understanding of the financial world and the tools used to analyze and interpret the different transactions being made and the terms used to describe them.
Relevant introductory material for corporate finance
This course did a good job of teaching the accounting and financial principles present in financial institutions, specifically for valuing firms and projects.
Very useful knowledge for anyone interested in Finance.
I learned how to perform many types of financial calculations and about the field in general.
Great introductory course to corporate finance and firm valuation. Insights of how the firm is evaluated in the market, how stocks, bonds, and other financial instruments work.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Professor Jose is really trying to get the students to learn, which is very helpful. On the other hand, the subject is, a lot of times, very dry and it becomes easy to just lose the thought process of the class.
Maybe less topics, but more depth.
The material covered was interesting and the textbook was excellent but the in class instruction left a lot to be desired. I learned everything from reading the book.
A little bit tedious and with lots of formulae that sometimes makes it hard to get.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, because the ideas are interesting and the terms and tools useful. But, if possible, I would recommend it Credit/D/Fail, because it is not easy.
Very useful for those interested in Finance carreers.
Great course if you don't know anything about corporate finance. It's useful for life.
